description.en: The Building Element Ontology provides an ontology based on the IfcBuildingElement subtree in the IFC specification, containing a taxonomy of classes that allow to define common building elements.

comment.en:
A component of the construction that normally encloses a space vertically. May provide the lower support (floor) or upper construction (roof slab) in any space in a building.
Only the core or constructional part of this construction is considered to be a slab. The upper finish (flooring, roofing) and the lower finish (ceiling, suspended ceiling) are considered to be coverings.
